author: Paige Steele
text: Also pretty ironic that releasing these types of videos is literally the only request from the public that they give in to? I can think of a lot of things the public is actually demanding—affordable healthcare, housing and education equality, etc. Why can’t we get any of that?

author: Paige Steele
text: There’s no need to view any of these videos unless you’re directly involved with the criminal/civil case. “They” say they release the videos because “the public is demanding to see it” which actually translates to—the public’s clicks and views = $$$$

author: Paige Steele
text: Begging everyone to NOT watch the Adam Toledo video. Respect his family. Respect that he was a 13-year-old *child* with a developing brain. This goes for any video of any murder—it’s sad how desensitized we’ve become & how easy it is to find videos of people being murdered online
